245
00:16:23,541 --> 00:16:25,000
WITHOUT A HITCH.

246
00:16:25,083 --> 00:16:27,875
YOU HAVE TO HAND IT TO HIM,
HIS TIMING WAS PERFECT.

247
00:16:27,958 --> 00:16:31,333
AND IT WAS ALL DUE TO HIS
ONE-HANDED STEERING TECHNIQUE.

248
00:16:31,416 --> 00:16:33,291
EVEN IF WE KNEW ALL ABOUT IT
BEFORE WE GOT HERE,

249
00:16:33,375 --> 00:16:35,791
WE NEVER COULDN'T HAVE
AVOIDED THIS.

250
00:16:35,875 --> 00:16:38,208
- Man: ALRIGHT, YOU DID IT!
YOU DID IT!

251
00:16:38,291 --> 00:16:39,875
- ( people cheering )

252
00:16:43,083 --> 00:16:44,375
- THIS FREAKIN' SUCKS, MAN!

253
00:16:44,458 --> 00:16:46,500
WHAT THE HELL DOES FUJIWARA
THINK HE'S DOIN'?

254
00:16:46,583 --> 00:16:47,583
KEISUKE WON THE HILL CLIMB

255
00:16:47,666 --> 00:16:49,458
AND NOW HE'S SCREWING
UP THE DOWNHILL!

256
00:16:49,541 --> 00:16:53,083
- HE GOT PASSED.
HAD TO HAPPEN SOONER OR LATER.

257
00:16:53,166 --> 00:16:55,000
- AND NOW THERE'S NOTHING
WE CAN DO!

258
00:16:55,083 --> 00:16:56,958
THERE'S NO WAY WE'RE GONNA
WIN ON THE DOWNHILL!

259
00:16:57,041 --> 00:16:59,083
WE'RE TOTALLY HOSED!

260
00:16:59,166 --> 00:17:01,541
- IS THAT WHAT YOU THINK?

261
00:17:01,625 --> 00:17:04,166
IF THERE WAS ANYONE ELSE BEHIND
THE WHEEL OF THAT EIGHT-SIX,

262
00:17:04,250 --> 00:17:05,333
I'D AGREE.

263
00:17:05,416 --> 00:17:08,541
BUT THERE'S NOT.
THAT'S FUJIWARA DRIVING.

264
00:17:09,916 --> 00:17:12,333
NO WAY TO TELL WHAT'S HE'S GONNA
TRY TO PULL NEXT.

265
00:17:12,416 --> 00:17:14,375
- I GUESS YOU'RE RIGHT, BUT...

266
00:17:17,833 --> 00:17:20,750
- MAYBE IT'S JUST THAT
I DON'T WANT YOU TO LOSE.

267
00:17:20,833 --> 00:17:23,708
IF ANYBODY DESERVES TO
SHOW YOU UP IN A BATTLE,

268
00:17:23,791 --> 00:17:25,875
DAMN IT, IT'S GOT TO BE ME.

269
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:32,333
- JOSHIMA'S TECHNIQUE IS
SO PERFECTED THAT IT BECOMES

270
00:17:32,416 --> 00:17:33,916
HARMFUL TO A DRIVER
LIKE FUJIWARA

271
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:35,541
WHO OPERATES MOSTLY ON INSTINCT.

272
00:17:35,625 --> 00:17:37,708
THEIR TYPES DON'T
MESH WELL TOGETHER.

273
00:17:37,791 --> 00:17:40,416
BEFORE HE KNOWS WHAT'S GOING ON,
HE'S SYNCED UP.

274
00:17:40,500 --> 00:17:42,291
THEN HE'S PULLED ALONG
FOR THE RIDE.

275
00:17:42,375 --> 00:17:44,750
I KNEW FROM THE GET-GO
THIS WOULD HAPPEN.

276
00:17:44,833 --> 00:17:46,791
THERE WAS NEVER A DOUBT
IN MY MIND.

277
00:17:46,875 --> 00:17:50,166
BUT NOW THE STALEMATE IS BROKEN,
PRACTICALLY ANYTHING CAN HAPPEN.

278
00:17:50,250 --> 00:17:53,666
- ( gasps ) I DON'T GET IT.
WHAT DO YOU MEAN, IT'S BROKEN?

279
00:17:53,750 --> 00:17:55,958
- FUJIWARA'S FREED
FROM BEING CONTROLLED.

280
00:17:56,041 --> 00:17:58,375
HE CAN REGAIN HIS OWN PACE
AND FINISH OUT THE BATTLE

281
00:17:58,458 --> 00:17:59,791
IN HIS OWN WAY.

282
00:18:01,708 --> 00:18:04,833
MAY LOOK GRIM AT THE MOMENT
BUT THEY HAVEN'T BEATEN US YET.

283
00:18:13,375 --> 00:18:15,500
- TIME TO LEAVE THIS KID
IN THE DUST.

284
00:18:15,583 --> 00:18:19,291
NO POINT IN SAVING
MY TIRES ANYMORE.

285
00:18:19,375 --> 00:18:21,083
I'LL USE THE REST OF MY GRIP

286
00:18:21,166 --> 00:18:23,875
AND LEAVE YOU WONDERING
WHERE I WENT.

287
00:19:08,125 --> 00:19:09,375
- ( crowd cheering )

288
00:19:13,416 --> 00:19:16,416
- DID YOU SEE THAT? THE
EIGHT-SIX WAS BEHIND JOSHIMA.

289
00:19:16,500 --> 00:19:20,875
- YEAH. IT DOESN'T MAKE SENSE.
HOW'D HE EVEN DO THAT?

290
00:19:25,666 --> 00:19:27,791
- KEEP IN MIND, THE EIGHT-SIX
ISN'T THE ONLY CAR

291
00:19:27,875 --> 00:19:30,291
WEARING DOWN ITS TIRES TONIGHT.

292
00:19:30,375 --> 00:19:32,333
THAT S-TWO THOUSAND IS
A LITTLE HEAVIER.

293
00:19:32,416 --> 00:19:34,875
THAT'LL DO ITS OWN DAMAGE.

294
00:19:34,958 --> 00:19:36,458
- YOU GOT A POINT THERE.

295
00:19:36,541 --> 00:19:38,791
- IT DOESN'T MATTER HOW SKILLED
YOU ARE AT MANAGING YOUR TIRES,

296
00:19:38,875 --> 00:19:40,125
THERE'S A PHYSICAL LIMIT.

297
00:19:40,208 --> 00:19:43,291
IT'S TRUE YOU CAN ONLY DO
SO MUCH FOR SO LONG.

298
00:19:43,375 --> 00:19:46,208
THAT TIME IS GOING TO COME
FOR OUR OPPONENT AS WELL.

299
00:19:46,291 --> 00:19:49,041
IT'S NOT LIKE HIS TIRES
ARE EXEMPT.

300
00:19:49,125 --> 00:19:50,375
AND UNDER THOSE CONDITIONS,

301
00:19:50,458 --> 00:19:53,416
THE EIGHT-SIX ACTUALLY HAS
MANY MORE ADVANTAGES.

302
00:19:55,416 --> 00:19:57,833
WE KNOW THAT JOSHIMA'S
ONE-HANDED STYLE OF STEERING

303
00:19:57,916 --> 00:19:59,041
IS HIS BIG THING.

304
00:19:59,125 --> 00:20:00,875
THAT'S HIS GOLDEN EGG.

305
00:20:00,958 --> 00:20:02,541
BUT THE FACT THAT
HE'S SO COMFORTABLE ENOUGH

306
00:20:02,625 --> 00:20:05,250
TO CONTINUE DRIVING WITH
ONE HAND MEANS ONE THING.

307
00:20:05,333 --> 00:20:06,833
THAT AS HARD AS
TAKUMI'S BEEN TRYING

308
00:20:06,916 --> 00:20:07,916
TO THROW HIM OFF HIS GAME,

309
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:10,000
HE'S STILL SQUARELY
IN HIS ELEMENT.

310
00:20:10,083 --> 00:20:11,500
- OKAY, BUT WHAT'S YOUR POINT?

311
00:20:11,583 --> 00:20:13,375
- WHEN SOMETHING JARRING
HAPPENS IN A RACE,

312
00:20:13,458 --> 00:20:16,291
MOST DRIVERS INSTINCTIVELY
GRAB THE WHEEL WITH BOTH HANDS.

313
00:20:16,375 --> 00:20:19,250
MY POINT IS THAT HE'S CONFIDENT
THAT NOTHING LIKE THAT

314
00:20:19,333 --> 00:20:21,291
WOULD EVER HAPPEN TO HIM
WHILE HE'S IN THIS BATTLE.

315
00:20:22,833 --> 00:20:25,041
- COOL, I GET
WHAT YOU'RE SAYIN'.

316
00:20:25,125 --> 00:20:28,125
- WHEN RACING, THIS GUY CAN
INTUIT WHAT'S COMIN' UP NEXT.

317
00:20:28,208 --> 00:20:30,083
THAT'S WHY IT APPEARS HE
KNOW HOW TO PREDICT

318
00:20:30,166 --> 00:20:32,291
EXACTLY WHAT'S
AROUND EACH CORNER.

319
00:20:32,375 --> 00:20:35,208
HE'S CONFIDENT THAT EVERYTHING
WILL GO HIS WAY.

320
00:20:35,291 --> 00:20:38,125
THAT ALLOWS HIM TO USE
HIS ONE-HANDED STEERING.

321
00:20:38,208 --> 00:20:40,125
WE HAVE TO BREAK
THAT CONFIDENCE.

322
00:20:40,208 --> 00:20:41,583
WE CAN'T AFFORD TO LOSE.

323
00:20:41,666 --> 00:20:42,750
AND NOW THAT WE KNOW THIS

324
00:20:42,833 --> 00:20:45,083
WE CERTAINLY CAN'T AFFORD
TO DO NOTHING.

325
00:20:45,166 --> 00:20:47,625
IF WE CAN'T CREATE A SITUATION
THAT FORCES THE ISSUE,

326
00:20:47,708 --> 00:20:49,125
SOMETHING THAT SCARES HIM
TO THE POINT

327
00:20:49,208 --> 00:20:51,208
THAT HE GRABS THE WHEEL
WITH BOTH HANDS,

328
00:20:51,291 --> 00:20:53,125
WE WON'T BE ABLE TO
CREATE AN OPENING.

329
00:20:56,166 --> 00:20:57,625
WE MIGHT BE ABLE
TO EDGE HIM OUT,

330
00:20:57,708 --> 00:20:59,625
BUT WE'LL NEED TO
GET INSIDE HIS HEAD

331
00:20:59,708 --> 00:21:02,750
THE SAME WAY HE TRIED TO
FORCE HIS WAY INTO TAKUMI'S.

332
00:21:02,833 --> 00:21:04,666
