YOU DOING BACK THERE, KID?

335
00:22:00,041 --> 00:22:01,541
- THERE'S NO NEED
TO MATCH HIS PACE.

336
00:22:01,625 --> 00:22:03,291
JUST RELAX AND DO YOU OWN THING.

337
00:22:03,375 --> 00:22:05,833
YOUR BEST SHOT IS TO
TAKE THE COUNTER-OFFENSIVE.

338
00:22:05,916 --> 00:22:07,375
YOU SHOULD'VE ALREADY
NOTICED THAT YOU CAN USE

339
00:22:07,458 --> 00:22:08,875
THE GUTTERS AND HEDGES
ON THIS COURSE.

340
00:22:08,958 --> 00:22:11,708
YOU NEED TO TAKE ADVANTAGE
OF THAT WHEN YOU CAN.

341
00:22:11,791 --> 00:22:14,000
I DON'T THINK I NEED TO REMIND
YOU OF EVERYTHING PROJECT D

342
00:22:14,083 --> 00:22:15,875
HAS RIDING ON THIS.

343
00:22:31,083 --> 00:22:33,666
- THERE IT IS.
THAT'S WHAT HE'S GUNNING FOR.

344
00:22:45,583 --> 00:22:48,250
HE'S GONE. BUT HOW?

345
00:23:02,875 --> 00:23:04,125
WHAT THE HELL?

346
00:23:04,208 --> 00:23:06,875
- ♪ I JUST WANNA BE
THE ONE FOR YOU ♪

347
00:23:06,958 --> 00:23:10,291
♪ I JUST WANNA BE THE ONE
WHO LOVES YOU ♪

348
00:23:24,208 --> 00:23:25,833
- WHAT HAPPENED BACK THERE?

349
00:23:28,625 --> 00:23:31,166
- ♪ GIVE ME A SIGN
THAT WILL KEEP ME ALIVE ♪

350
00:23:31,250 --> 00:23:34,291
♪ IN THIS HOPELESS
CRUEL, CRUEL WORLD ♪

351
00:23:34,375 --> 00:23:37,333
- WAIT. I'M GOING CRAZY.
OR DID I JUST SEE THAT?

352
00:23:37,416 --> 00:23:39,250
- I DON'T KNOW ABOUT
YOU BUT I JUST SAW

353
00:23:39,333 --> 00:23:46,333
A SECOND SET OF HEADLIGHTS
POP UP OUTTA FREAKIN' NOWHERE.

354
00:23:46,416 --> 00:23:48,916
- DAMN IT! I LOSE SIGHT OF HIM
FOR ONE SECOND

355
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:51,250
AND SUDDENLY THE KID COMES AT ME
FROM THE SHARPEST ANGLE

356
00:23:51,333 --> 00:23:52,708
HE CAN EVEN ATTEMPT.

357
00:23:52,791 --> 00:23:56,291
NOW THAT'S A GOD-LIKE
DRIVING TECHNIQUE.

358
00:23:56,375 --> 00:23:58,041
I HAD AN IDEA
HE WAS CORNERING

359
00:23:58,125 --> 00:23:59,791
BY USING THE GUTTERS
BY THE HEDGES,

360
00:23:59,875 --> 00:24:01,958
BUT I DECIDED I MUST BE CRAZY,

361
00:24:02,041 --> 00:24:05,333
IT'S SUCH AN INCREDIBLY
RISKY TECHNIQUE.

362
00:24:05,416 --> 00:24:07,958
IF HE MISSED HIS TIMING BY
EVEN A FRACTION OF A SECOND,

363
00:24:08,041 --> 00:24:10,958
HE'D LOSE CONTROL AND
CRASH INTO THE MOUNTAIN.

364
00:24:11,041 --> 00:24:13,291
AND MY CAR'S BEEN LOWERED
AS FAR AS IT CAN,

365
00:24:13,375 --> 00:24:16,416
SO I COULDN'T COPY HIS MOVE
EVEN IF I WANTED TO.

366
00:24:16,500 --> 00:24:19,208
WHAT HE'S DOING IS
TAILOR-MADE FOR AN OLDER CAR

367
00:24:19,291 --> 00:24:23,000
WITHOUT ANYTHING HANGING FROM
ITS UNDERCARRIAGE. WELL PLAYED.

368
00:24:24,875 --> 00:24:26,250
- I DON'T KNOW HOW TO
TELL YOU THIS,

369
00:24:26,333 --> 00:24:29,583
BUT JOSHIMA JUST GOT PASSED.

370
00:24:29,666 --> 00:24:33,833
- YOU MEAN THAT DOCTOR GOD FOOT
TOUSHIMO WAS BEATEN BY SOME KID?

371
00:24:33,916 --> 00:24:35,333
- IT'S LIKE I WAS TELLIN' YOU.

372
00:24:35,416 --> 00:24:38,291
WE GOT NO IDEA WHAT'LL
HAPPEN IN THIS BATTLE.

373
00:24:38,375 --> 00:24:40,750
THAT'S JUST THE WAY FUJIWARA IS.

